description:
Blender 2.46 was released not long ago, and packs a ton of new features, including a completely rewritten particle system, as well as a new image browser, cloth simulation, and more.

This is the final release for Windows 98, ME, 2000, XP, and Vista.  It was built on Python 2.5, which, if you don&amp;#039;t have it, can be downloaded for free at python.org/download

If you&amp;#039;re new to Blender, you might want to follow this link to see what it&amp;#039;s capable of:
  &lt;a href=&quot;
http://www.blender.org/features-gallery/gallery/images/&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot; target=&quot;_NEW&quot;&gt;
http://www.blender.org/features-gallery/gallery/images/&lt;/a&gt;

And then you&amp;#039;ll want to follow this link to learn how to use it:
  &lt;a href=&quot;
http://wiki.blender.org/index.php/Manual/Your_First_Animation_in_30_plus_30_Minutes_Part_I&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot; target=&quot;_NEW&quot;&gt;
http://wiki.blender.org/index.php/Manual/Your_First_Animation_in_30_plus_30_Minutes_Part_I&lt;/a&gt;

Blender is, as always, completely free and open source.  Enjoy!
